Background

		Ms. Adrianne Shapira served as the Chief Financial Officer of David Yurman Enterprises LLC, a fine jewelry luxury brand, since October 2012 until February 2016. Ms. Shapira served as an Analyst of Goldman Sachs Group Inc., Research Division until September 11, 2012. From September 1999 to September 2012, Ms. Shapira served as Managing Director of The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc., where she was an Equity Research Analyst and covered the discount, department store, dollar ... store, warehouse club, apparel manufacturer, luxury and grocery sectors. Ms. Shapira was an Equity Analyst at Neuberger & Berman, an investment management company. She has significant experience as an Equity Analyst in sectors. Ms. Shapira has strong financial expertise, as well a broad understanding of the consumer products industry. She had a 13-year tenure at Goldman Sachs. She served as an Equity Analyst of Robertson Stephens, Inc., Research Division, Barclays PLC, Research Division and Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc., Research Division. She was a Lead Equity Analyst and covered department stores, discounters, luxury and online. She covered stocks at Neuberger & Berman, an investment management company. She has been a Director at The Hain Celestial Group, Inc. since November 20, 2014. She has been an Independent Director of Kohl's Corporation since August 10, 2016. She has been a Director of Gilt Groupe, Inc. since June 30, 2014. She holds MBA from Columbia Business School and a BA from Tufts University.Read Full Background




