Adrianne Shapira

           Chief Financial Officer, David Yurman
           
Adrianne Shapira is the Chief Financial Officer of David Yurman, a fine jewelry luxury brand. Adrianne is a member of the Executive Committee that seeks to build upon David Yurman's successes by capitalizing on future channel, category and geographic growth. Prior to joining David Yurman in October 2012, Adrianne had a thirteen year tenure at Goldman Sachs, where she was Managing Director in Global Investment Research covering the Broadlines Retail sector. She was the lead equity analyst covering department stores, discounters, luxury and online. Prior to joining Goldman Sachs, Adrianne covered stocks at Neuberger & Berman, an investment management company.
Adrianne earned an MBA from Columbia Business School and a BA from Tufts University. She lives in Manhattan with her husband and two sons. 



















